docs.source_name: Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development
docs.name: Euro Area Bread And Cereals (5)
docs.description: This dataset contains the main results of the 2008 Eurostat-OECD PPP comparison for the 46 countries that participated in the 2008 round of the Eurostat-OECD Purchasing Power Parity (PPP) Programme and for the 5 countries that participated in the CIS (Commonwealth of Independent States) Comparison Programme for 2008. The OECD makes comparisons every three years when Eurostat makes them every year. The last benchmark year is 2005 and data are available in the dataset 2005 PPP Benchmark results. The next benchmark year will be 2011 and results will be released end 2013. The PPP results presented here have been calculated following a methodology agreed by Eurostat and the OECD. All detailed information can be found in the Eurostat-OECD Methodological Manual on Purchasing Power Parities. The methodology employed for CIS comparisons is closely aligned with that of Eurostat and the OECD. More info at http://stats.oecd.org/OECDStat_Metadata/ShowMetadata.ashx?Dataset=PPP2008&Lang=en.

docs.source_name: United Nations
docs.name: Employed Population by Status - Male / Age 40 to 44 - Poland
docs.description: The United Nations Demographic Yearbook collects, compiles and disseminates official statistics on a wide range of topics. Data have been collected from national statistical authorities since 1948 through a set of questionnaires dispatched annually by the United Nations Statistics Division to over 230 national statistical offices. The Demographic Yearbook disseminates statistics on population size and composition, births, deaths, marriage and divorce on an annual basis. Demographic Yearbook special topics issues cover a wide range of additional topics including economic activity, educational attainment, household characteristics, housing, ethnicity and language, among others.
